channel.title: How would i export a model to .3ds using RSMV V3.0?
channel.description:
Well basically i downloaded RSMV v3.0 and it rules lol. :D
But i was wondering how i would export the runescape model to a .3ds model? it has the option under "File/Export" but its not enabled on any models i look at.
Any help? ;)
Or is there a way to convert a .dat file to .3ds or .max?

item.dc:creator: @silabsoft RuneAgent
item.description:
@silabsoft wrote:

so not true, it has nothing to do with textures at all, their is now two formats they seem to have discontinued the first format completely anything new coming out is in format two, because it has extended texturing abilitys

http://silabsoft.no-ip.org:8080/servlet/Model?type=text&id=30000 - http://silabsoft.no-ip.org:8080/servlet/Model?type=text&id=31000

all model format 2.0

also if you want any model converted i currently offer obj and wrl formats

http://silabsoft.no-ip.org:8080/servlet/Model?type=obj&id=30000
http://silabsoft.no-ip.org:8080/servlet/Model?type=vrml&id=30000

both work fine in just about every model editor i have used.
